{"id": "duc04-testb-23:11#34", "contents": "The Brazilian government's enormous deficits have made it particularly vulnerable to the collapse of emerging markets, which has drained foreign currency reserves and pushed the economy towards recession. Finance officials in Washington and around the world fear that a collapse of Brazil would worsen financial instability throughout the hemisphere, given its size and links to other economies. As the world's ninth-largest economy and the financial engine of Latin America, Brazil's economic health is of great concern. Throughout the day, government officials met with President Fernando Henrique Cardoso in Brasilia to fine-tune a three-year austerity package, which Cardoso was to discuss with congressional party leaders on Wednesday morning."}
